    "summary": "These are not mere collateral damages; they represent the systematic destruction of civilian infrastructure, yet the discourse surrounding such events frequently navigates away from direct accountability, instead framing these actions within a broader narrative of necessity. My observations since February 23, 2026, reveal a consistent and deeply entrenched pattern: when state actions result in severe consequences, particularly those bordering on extrajudicial or exceeding conventional legal bounds, the prevailing narrative quickly shifts to one of justification. This justification is almost invariably rooted in concepts of public order, national security, or strategic imperative."
